<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-08T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-08T23:00:00-05:00" n="771" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2806: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-09T13:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">November 9,
                                        1922—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 9—3:30
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>190. Your 134, November 7, 5 p.m. Uchida informed me today the Japanese
                            Government has no objection to delay pending Stevens’ arrival
                            Washington.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>